{"title":"Discerning Temporal Difference Learning","domain":"RL","seeds":[{"problem":"Standard TD(λ) assigns uniform credit to historical states and propagates TD errors without considering state importance, which leads to biased or unstable value estimates under visitation imbalance or noisy outcomes.","method":"Introduce Discerning TD learning (DTD), which embeds a nonnegative emphasis function f(s) directly into a new discerning λ-return G_{λ,f} derived from a forward-view identity, then connects it to an efficient backward view. The resulting update reweights both history and error propagation via f: the eligibility trace accumulates as e ← γλ e + f(S)∇v̂(S,θ) and the parameter update is θ ← θ + α δ e f(S). DTD also minimizes an emphasized objective with Λ = F D F (F = diag(f)) and projection Π_f, effectively modulating the steady-state weighting by f^2 and enabling either predetermined or adaptive emphasis."},{"problem":"Emphasis-aware TD methods need stability guarantees, especially when the emphasis is state- or parameter-dependent.","method":"Define the discerning λ-return operator T_{λ,f} and prove it is a contraction for a function class Ξ: (i) under a norm bound on F for parameter-independent f; and (ii) under a Lipschitz condition on F(V_θ) for parameter-dependent f. Show Π_f T_{λ,f} remains a contraction, derive the associated deterministic variant with A = E[e(γϕ(S′)−ϕ(S))^⊤ f(S)] and b = E[e R f(S)], and prove DTD(λ) converges to a unique fixed point θ* satisfying Aθ* + b = 0 for any f ∈ Ξ."},{"problem":"Practitioners lack a compact, task-aligned way to set emphasis that improves learning under aliasing, limited representation, or noise.","method":"Use an adaptive, parameter-dependent emphasis defined as the absolute expected TD error (evaluated under the true dynamics) to align update magnitude with prediction difficulty. In experiments on 5-state random walk variants (tabular/inverted/dependent features) and the 13-state Boyan chain, as well as setups with visitation imbalance and perturbed rewards, this choice accelerates learning and reduces MSPBE versus TD(λ), on-policy ETD(λ), PTD, and TD(λ,w(·)); predetermined f(s) (e.g., inverse visitation or exp(−σ(s))) further rebalances updates and mitigates noise."}]}
